Definition: marked by defiant disregard for danger or consequences
Example: foolhardy enough to try to seize the gun from the hijacker; became the fiercest and most reckless of partisans-Macaulay; a reckless driver; a rash attempt to climb Mount Everest
Synonyms: noun, attribute, foolhardiness, heady, group, head, rash, rashness, reckless, recklessness, marked, by, defiant, disregard, for, danger, or, consequences, enough, to, try, seize, the, gun, from, hijacker, became, fiercest, and, most, of, partisans, -Macaulay, a, driver, attempt, climb, Mount, Everest
Category: adj.all
